SIMPLE: intrusion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intrusion
<hw>In*tru"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intrusion</ets>. See <er>Intrude</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of intruding, or of forcing in; especially,
the forcing (one's self) into a place without right or welcome;
encroachment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why this <qex>intrusion</qex>?⟦br⟧
Were not my orders that I should be private?</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The penetrating of one rock,
while in a plastic or metal state, into the cavities of
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The entry of a stranger, after a
particular estate or freehold is determined, before the person who holds
in remainder or reversion has taken possession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Scotch Ch.)</fld> <def>The settlement of a minister
over a congregation without their consent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrusional</ent>⟦br⟧
